</strong></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-83_ pf-heading-1-h3">Some autistic individuals may have issues with melatonin production. This hormone is vital for regulating sleep, and irregularities can lead to difficulties falling asleep or staying asleep through the night.</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-85_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Anxiety and stress
