</strong></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-100_ pf-heading-1-h3">Create a predictable sleep schedule by setting consistent bedtimes and wake-up times. This regularity helps to regulate the body’s internal clock, making it easier to fall asleep and wake up naturally.</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-102_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Create a calming sleep environment
</strong></h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-eONOlN dawdJE pf-104_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-105_ pf-text-1"><strong>Lighting</strong> - Use dim lighting or blackout curtains to reduce exposure to light.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-107_ pf-text-1"><strong>Noise</strong> - Consider using white noise machines to mask disruptive sounds.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-bStdFM fgfEIw pf-109_ pf-text-1"><strong>Comfort </strong>- Opt for soft, sensory-friendly bedding. Weighted blankets might help provide comfort for some individuals.</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-111_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Develop a pre-sleep routine
</strong></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-113_ pf-heading-1-h3">Incorporate calming activities into a pre-sleep routine. Gentle activities like reading, taking a warm bath, or practising relaxation exercises can signal to the body that it’s time to wind down.</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-115_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Manage sensory inputs
</strong></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-117_ pf-heading-1-h3">Identify and address sensory sensitivities that might affect sleep. This might involve adjusting the bedroom environment to suit individual sensory needs, such as using earplugs or a sleep mask if needed.</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-119_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Limit stimulants and screen time
</strong></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-121_ pf-heading-1-h3">Avoid caffeine and sugary foods close to bedtime. Additionally, reduce screen time at least an hour before bed to prevent blue light from interfering with melatonin production.</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-iLLNPL gTJAOY pf-123_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Promote physical activity
